SINGLE-FLUID 2D HYDROSTATIC TEST
--------------------------------

Single inviscid fluid at rest in a [-5,5]^2 domain subject to gravity.
Fluid should remain at rest, with a linear pressure field.

With rho=2, g=(0,-1,0), p = const - 2*y.

Variations use rotated meshes (and rotated g)

&OUTPUTS
  output_t  = 0.0, 2.0
  output_dt = 2.0
/

&MESH
  mesh_file = 'mesh1.gen'
/

&PHYSICS
  materials = 'water'
  flow = .true.
  body_force_density = 0.0, -1.0, 0.0
/

&FLOW
  inviscid = .true.
  courant_number = 0.5
/

&FLOW_PRESSURE_SOLVER
  rel_tol = 0.0
  abs_tol = 1.0e-12
  max_ds_iter = 50
  max_amg_iter = 25
  krylov_method = 'cg'
/

&NUMERICS
  dt_constant = 0.125
/

# FREE SLIP BC ALL AROUND
&FLOW_BC
  name = 'all sides'
  face_set_ids = 1, 2, 3, 4, 5
  type = 'free-slip'
/

&BODY
  surface_name = 'from mesh file'
  mesh_material_number = 1
  material_name = 'water'
  velocity = 3*0.0
  temperature = 0.0
/

&BODY
  surface_name = 'from mesh file'
  mesh_material_number = 2
  material_name = 'water'
  velocity = 3*0.0
  temperature = 0.0
/

&MATERIAL
  name = 'water'
  is_fluid = T
  density = 2.0
  specific_heat = 1.0
/
